article.description: — Abou Ousmane had a career-high 22 points plus 11 rebounds as North Texas narrowly beat Marshall 69-65 on Thursday night.
article.headline: Ousmane scores 22 to lead North Texas past Marshall 69-65
article.linkText: Ousmane scores 22 to lead North Texas past Marshall 69-65
article.story: HUNTINGTON, W.Va. -- — Abou Ousmane had a career-high 22 points plus 11 rebounds as North Texas narrowly beat Marshall 69-65 on Thursday night. Tylor Perry had 12 points and six rebounds for North Texas (10-4, 3-1 Conference USA). JJ Murray added 11 points and Thomas Bell had 10 points, 12 rebounds, five assists and three blocks. Taevion Kinsey had 29 points for the Thundering Herd (7-9, 0-3), whose losing streak stretched to six games. Darius George added 18 points. ------ For more AP college basketball coverage: https://apnews.com/hub/college-basketball and http://twitter.com/AP--Top25 ------ This was generated by Automated Insights, http://www.automatedinsights.com/ap, using data from STATS LLC, https://www.stats.com
